-- Brazilian Stock Movers: Brasil Brokers, CSN, Embraer Were Active
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 2012-03-21T20:38:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-21/brazilian-stock-movers-brasil-brokers-csn-embraer-are-active.html
The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  index lost 0.6 percent to 66,860.05.  Brasil Brokers Participacoes SA (BBRK3)  (BBRK3 BS) fell 4.6 percent
to 7.22 reais, the biggest decline in four months. The real
estate brokerage reported 2011 adjusted net income of 107
million reais ($58.6 million), trailing the average estimate for
125 million reais among seven analysts surveyed by Bloomberg.  Cia. Siderurgica Nacional SA (CSNA3)  (CSNA3 BS) declined 3.7
percent to 18.54 reais, the biggest drop since Dec. 8.  Brazil ’s
third-largest steelmaker was cut to the equivalent of sell from
neutral by analysts including Leonardo Correa at Barclays Plc.
The analysts cited sluggish growth at the company’s mining unit
and said CSN’s outperformance relative to Vale SA is
unjustified.  Embraer SA (EMBR3)  (EMBR3 BS) gained 4 percent to 14.20 reais, the
highest in more than a year. The world’s fourth-largest plane
maker said sales rose 9.7 percent in the fourth quarter to 3.67
billion reais, above the estimates of all three analysts
surveyed by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
